3 I really wanted to like this place, but I was torn between giving Scratch 2 stars or 3 stars.  Let's start off with the good:  I love the decor, and my 7-month-old daughter loved the hot pink rubber "doily" placemats.  :)  Also, the pastries looked amazing.  Finally, tons of parking available.  On to the negatives:  1.  One server for about 25 patrons.  2.  Food took forever to be cooked and then to be served to me.  3.  In what the server referred to as "the chef getting creative," they served my (undercooked) hash browns on top of my (cold) scrambled eggs... and the grease from said hash browns sunk into said eggs.  Bweck.    I will go back one more time to eat the pastries, and even if they are great, I might have to stick to my 3-star rating.
5 Scratch was recommended by the staff at nearby Hotel Indigo.  It was a good call!  Less than a 10-minute walk from the hotel, Scratch was exactly what my gf and I were looking for.  With a mostly organic menu of not just pastries but all-day food (I had a burger, she had a quiche), it was perfect for an early lunch or late breakfast.  The owner even came out to meet us after our meal just to chat for a few minutes, find out where we were from and how we heard about the place, and even had some suggestions for checking out local artwork.  It was exactly the kind of service that most establishments don't have the time or patience to offer their patrons.  The only "con" was the view: there was none, as it was situated in the corner of a large shopping center parking lot.  But where it lacked view, it had great food and friendly staff.  I definitely recommend it if you're in the area.
