4 We've done breakfast and dinner here.  Breakfast was punctuated by that awesome airy bakery smell, fresh orange juice, great coffee, excellent service, and gourmet breakfast sandwiches. Lots of people love to rave about the Breakfast Club in Scottsdale but sorry for me, Scratch has it beat.... clobbered even.  Dinner was also an excellent treat punctuated with great service and great food. The duck was crispy but not greasy and the potatoes were cooked very well but needed a pinch of salt and a little more seasoning overall.
5 We stopped in for lunch and really enjoyed the vegan burger, but added real cheese. It was great and so was the salad that came with it. We also ordered coffee and a delicious dirty chai.  Service was very friendly and helpful with all of our questions. The chef was willing to prepare a dish that was not on the current menu, but did appear on the website. We ordered the Savory Napolean, which is a puff pastry filled with two (or more) fillings that can also be ordered in crepe or omelet form. It was quite good, although we did add a bit of salt. It would also probably be better with a more sharp cheese.  We ended the meal with a praline & chocolate macaroon, which we really enjoyed. We also took home one of the chocolate & peanut butter mousse for dessert later.  A lot of other reviews mention the cost and I was a little surprised at the price of the macaroon, but really the food was reasonable and so was the coffee. If you want cheap food, then you should probably go somewhere else, but in a town with so many chains I will gladly pay a little more to frequent a small business with a nice atmosphere.
